INSERT INTO courses (course_code, course_name, credits, gpa, subject, term, prerequisite_text, corequisite_text, enrollment_notes, course_description) VALUES ('0075A', 'AP Seminar A', 0.5, 5, 'English Language Arts', 'Semester 1', NULL, NULL, 'Students must complete the full credit for this course to satisfy the communication skills', 'AP Seminar is an interdisciplinary course that uses an inquiry approach to engage students in conversations that explore the complexities of academic and real -world topics and issues by analyzing varying perspectives. Students will consider issues through a variety of lenses and from multiple perspectives, many of which are divergent or competing. Students will participate in collaborative and independent performance tasks and an end-of-course exam to earn AP credit. AP Seminar is the first required course for the AP Capstone Diploma program. Students must complete the full credit in order for this course to satisfy the communication skills component and to continue to AP Research. Available only at campuses which applied to and were approved by College Board to offer this course. Can be taken as an Elective.') ON CONFLICT (course_code) DO NOTHING

INSERT INTO courses (course_code, course_name, credits, gpa, subject, term, prerequisite_text, corequisite_text, enrollment_notes, course_description) VALUES ('0077A', 'AP Research A', 0.5, 5, 'English Language Arts', 'Semester 1', '0075A', NULL, NULL, 'AP Research, the second course in the AP Capstone experience, allows students to deeply explore an academic topic, problem, issue, or idea of individual interest. Students design, plan, and implement a yearlong investigation to address a research question. Through this inquiry, students further the skills they acquired in the AP Seminar course by learning research methodology, employing ethical research practices, and accessing, analyzing, and synthesizing information. Students reflect on their skill development, document their processes, and curate the artifacts of their scholarly work through a process and reflection portfolio. The course culminates in an academic paper of 4,000 - 5,000 words (accompanied by a performance, exhibit, or product where applicable) and a presentation with an oral defense. Can be taken as an Elective.') ON CONFLICT (course_code) DO NOTHING

INSERT INTO courses (course_code, course_name, credits, gpa, subject, term, prerequisite_text, corequisite_text, enrollment_notes, course_description) VALUES ('0080A', 'Peer Assistance and Leadership 1A', 0.5, 4, 'Elective', 'Semester 1', NULL, NULL, 'Students must complete an application and be accepted into the PAL program before registering for this', 'This course develops student leaders who serve as trained peer mentors and role models. PALs work with students on their own campus as well as in feeder middle and elementary schools, building connections that foster confidence, resilien ce, and a sense of belonging. Through their influence, PALs create a more positive school culture while gaining valuable skills in communication, leadership, and problem -solving ‚Äîexperience that benefits them now and in future careers such as teaching, counseling , and other helping professions. Can be taken as an Elective.') ON CONFLICT (course_code) DO NOTHING

INSERT INTO courses (course_code, course_name, credits, gpa, subject, term, prerequisite_text, corequisite_text, enrollment_notes, course_description) VALUES ('0211A', '*Algebra 1 A', 0.5, 4, 'Math', 'Semester 1', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'In this course, students will study linear, quadratic, and exponential functions and make connections between the functions, their related transformations, equations and their solutions in both mathematical and real- world situations. Katy ISD high school campuses currently use the TI-Nspire CX II calculator or Desmos, a free online graphing calculator. Students may access Desmos on any device with internet. If purchasing their own calculator, students should select one that offers the capabilities and features of the TI -Nspire CX II. Note: Beginning with the class of 2029, the grade for Algebra 1 will not count towards a student‚Äôs grade point average (GPA) if the student successfully completes 4 math credits in addition to successfully completing Algebra 1.') ON CONFLICT (course_code) DO NOTHING

INSERT INTO courses (course_code, course_name, credits, gpa, subject, term, prerequisite_text, corequisite_text, enrollment_notes, course_description) VALUES ('0230A', 'AP Precalculus A', 0.5, 5, 'Math', 'Semester 1', '0223A or 0261A', NULL, 'Students who take AP Precalculus are not eligible to take Precalculus as the TEKS in Precalculus are duplicate in AP Precalculus.', 'This course emphasizes a conceptual understanding of functions and their graphs and covers polynomial and rational functions, exponential and logarithmic functions, trigonometric and polar functions, and general functions involving parameters, vectors, and matrices. Students enrolled in an Advanced Placement course are expected to take the corresponding AP exam. Calculators are available to students for in-class use when appropriate based on instruction. Katy ISD Advanced Placement math courses currently use the TI-Nspire CX II calculator or Desmos, a free online graphing calculator. If purchasing their own calculator, students should select one that offers the capabilities and features of the TI-Nspire CX II and is on the approved College Board calculator list.') ON CONFLICT (course_code) DO NOTHING

INSERT INTO courses (course_code, course_name, credits, gpa, subject, term, prerequisite_text, corequisite_text, enrollment_notes, course_description) VALUES ('0230VIRIDA', 'AP Precalculus A - VirInstDay', 0.5, 5, 'Math', 'Semester 1', NULL, NULL, 'Students who take AP Precalculus are not eligible to take Precalculus as the TEKS in Precalculus are duplicate in AP Precalculus.', 'This course emphasizes a conceptual understanding of functions and their graphs and covers polynomial and rational functions, exponential and logarithmic functions, trigonometric and polar functions, and general functions involving parameters, vectors, and matrices. Students enrolled in an Advanced Placement course are expected to take the corresponding AP exam. Calculators are available to students for in-class use when appropriate based on instruction. Katy ISD Advanced Placement math courses currently use the TI-Nspire CX II calculator or Desmos, a free online graphing calculator. If purchasing their own calculator, students should select one that offers the capabilities and features of the TI-Nspire CX II and is on the approved College Board calculator list.') ON CONFLICT (course_code) DO NOTHING

INSERT INTO courses (course_code, course_name, credits, gpa, subject, term, prerequisite_text, corequisite_text, enrollment_notes, course_description) VALUES ('0236A', '*Math Models with Applications A', 0.5, 5, 'Math', 'Semester 1', '0211A or 0223A', NULL, 'This course is a third math credit option for FHSPE students. INSERT INTO courses (course_code, course_name, credits, gpa, subject, term, prerequisite_text, corequisite_text, enrollment_notes, course_description) VALUES ('0316A', 'US History A (Dual Credit HIST 1301/1302)', 0.5, 4.5, 'Social Studies', 'Semester 1', NULL, NULL, 'HCC admissions requirements; TSI requirement. This course satisfies the US History high school graduation requirement. Students may not duplicate credit by taking AP, Academic, and Dual Credit US History courses**.**', 'The first semester traces the American nation from English colonization to the close of the Civil War through Reconstruction. The second semester covers the American nation from the end of the Reconstruction Era to the present. Students earn three college credit hours upon successful completion of each semester. Completing the full year course satisfies the high school US History graduation credit requirement. College Credit is provided by Houston Community College (HCC). NOTE: Due to the end-of-course (EOC) exam requirement, Dual Credit US History must be taken on a Katy ISD campus and cannot be taken during summer school. Can be taken as an Elective.') ON CONFLICT (course_code) DO NOTHING

INSERT INTO courses (course_code, course_name, credits, gpa, subject, term, prerequisite_text, corequisite_text, enrollment_notes, course_description) VALUES ('0335VIRF', 'Personal Financial Literacy (ELECT) - VirSup(Fall)', 0.5, 4, 'Social Studies', 'Semester 1', NULL, NULL, 'For the Classes of 2026‚Äì2028, this course is an elective and does not fulfill the Economics graduation requirement. Students in these cohorts may not earn credit for both the Personal Financial Literacy course and Economics and the Personal Financial Literacy elective course. Beginning with the Class of 2029 and all subsequent cohorts, completion of a Personal Financial Literacy course is required to meet graduation requirements. Students in the Class of 2029 and beyond may not enroll in Personal Financial Literacy and Economics or the semester-long Economics course.', 'This one-semester elective course is designed to help students develop the knowledge and skills to make sound, informed financial decisions that will allow them to become financially responsible.
